<strong>REFERENCE LIST ENTRY</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a reference list at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	Title of article. (Year, Month Day of publication). 
	<em>Title of Newspaper</em>, page number(s).
</blockquote>
<br>
If the work was accessed from a website (excluding online academic research databases, 
e.g., ProQuest, EBSCO and ScienceDirect) include the URL, displayed as an active link, 
at the end of the reference. Works accessed from an academic database do not require a URL 
or detail about the database in the reference list. In this case, the work would be referenced 
in the same manner as a print version of the work.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<span class="hover" title="Title of article">Hong Kong braces for protests</span>. 
	(<span class="hover" title="Year, Month Day of publication">2017, December 15</span>). 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of Newspaper">Melbourne Herald</span></em>, 
	<span class="hover" title="page number">A5</span>.
</blockquote>
